title: Roy Orbison - Dream Baby (Greatest Hits)(2013) Flac,Cue - ausy
description:
Although he shared the same rockabilly roots as Carl Perkins, Johnny Cash, and Elvis Presley,
 Roy Orbison went on to pioneer an entirely different brand of country/pop-based rock & roll in the early '60s.
 What he lacked in charisma and photogenic looks, Orbison made up for in spades with his quavering operatic voice 
and melodramatic narratives of unrequited love and yearning. In the process, he established rock & roll archetypes
 of the underdog and the hopelessly romantic loser. These were not only amplified by peers such as Del Shannon and 
Gene Pitney, but also influenced future generations of roots rockers such as Bruce Springsteen and Chris Isaak,
 as well as modern country stars the Mavericks.
